==English==
=== Etymology ===
From the French "ill ease"; ''[[mal]]'' "bad" + ''[[aise]]'' "ease"

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-malaise.ogg|Audio (US)}}

=== Noun ===
'''malaise'''
# a feeling of general [[bodily]] [[discomfort]] or [[unpleasantness]], often at the onset of [[illness]]
# an [[ambiguous]] feeling of [[mental]] or [[moral]] [[depression]]

==== Synonyms ====
*[[doldrums]]
*[[melancholy]]
*[[unease]]

